p0023 = "Then we chant the following Verses, doubling the first three and tripling the last, chanting it loudly and slowly:"
p0024 = "Direct my steps according to your word, and let no iniquity lord it over me. (Twice)"
p0025 = "Deliver me from the slander of men, and I shall keep your commandments. (Twice)"
p0026 = "Let your face shine on your servant, and teach me your statutes. (Twice)"
p0027 = "Let my mouth be filled with your praise, O Lord, that I may hymn your glory, all day long your splendour. (Three times)"
p0028 = "On the Monday, Wednesday and Friday of the 4th week of Lent, that is after the Sunday of the Veneration of the Cross, instead of the verses of Direct my steps, we say:"
p0029 = "We worship your Cross, O Master, and we glorify your holy Resurrection."
p0030 = "Then: Holy God, Holy Strong, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us (three times)"
